I think much of the resentment comes from the ridiculous Cult of Mac and Jobs'
god-like status amongst excessively image conscious types. His success largely
emanates from taking existing technology and making it shiny, desirable and
accessible to the masses. He didn't invent the wheel, he refashioned it, so
the hero-worship is a bit misplaced.

If it wasn't for OS X I wouldn't have bought a Mac. I realise they are
essentially overpriced PCs, but I'm prepared to bite the bullet and fork out
to get shut of Windows. I couldn't give a damn about iPads, iPods, iPhones or
iBogRoll. They're useless trinkets if you ask me.

